1
00:00:02,080 --> 00:00:04,280
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,120
<i>Don't treat me too well,</i>

3
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,240
<i>or I'll get spoiled.</i>

4
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:21,960
<i>I'm going to Bang Saen</i>
<i>to work on a school art project.</i>

5
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,720
<i>With who?</i>
<i>Do they like you?</i>

6
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:27,600
<i>I don't know if anyone has a crush on me.</i>

7
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:30,160
All I know is that my heart is yours.

8
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>Qin! Can we talk for a second?</i>

9
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,160
Are you with someone?

10
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:36,480
<i>I just want to talk to you.</i>

11
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:37,560
<i>You two were friends?</i>

12
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:40,480
<i>We weren't really</i>
<i>in the talking stage either.</i>

13
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,200
When he confessed how he felt about me.

14
00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:44,120
Since then, we rarely talked.

15
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:45,760
Was that mean?

16
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,120
You were.

17
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,200
But I never thought of you as a friend.

18
00:00:57,480 --> 00:01:00,680
We agreed we'd be in the talking stage.

19
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,040
You're still upset?

20
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,080
Yes.

21
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,160
We're in the talking stage.

22
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:39,840
Duang, just get to the point.

23
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,160
Don't be so harsh.

24
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,400
I'm not being harsh.

25
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,960
You're an overly possessive crybaby.

26
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,600
Take a shower with me tonight.

27
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,680
What did you just say?

28
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,520
I'm not going to say it twice.

29
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,280
Your fault if you missed it.

30
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,360
Ow! Hey!

31
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,320
That hurt.

32
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,560
Pretending you didn't hear that?

33
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,680
Playing hard to get?

34
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,360
Hey…

35
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,960
Stop clinging to my leg.

36
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,400
I'll let you shower with me,

37
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,600
but don't get any funny ideas.

38
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,040
No physical contact.

39
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:52,680
Understood?

40
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:54,840
Understood!

41
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,560
Right.

42
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,320
There's one more thing I want to say.

43
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,000
Tiw never got to shower with me.

44
00:04:55,840 --> 00:05:00,800
FOLLOWERS

45
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:06,880
<i>So he's your boyfriend, correct?</i>

46
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,080
What's it to you?

47
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,600
Just answer me.

48
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,520
I'm trying to be nice here.

49
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,440
<i>Duang's not just a friend.</i>

50
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,880
Where are you going? Come here.

51
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,360
Take a seat.

52
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,360
Hold him.

53
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,120
What's wrong?

54
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,280
I'm sure it's about Qin, not his grades.

55
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,080
I'll bet 10 baht.

56
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,240
- It's about Qin.
- No way.

57
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,240
Next time,
tell me the winning lottery number.

58
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,360
Shut it! I'm not a sacred entity.

59
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,280
Guys, listen to me first.

60
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,400
I met that guy.

61
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,640
Who?

62
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,480
It's the guy

63
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,000
who gave Qin the teddy bear.

64
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,560
Hold him.

65
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,760
Come.

66
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,480
Let me do a recap.

67
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,200
This bastard!

68
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:26,240
Duang…

69
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:30,080
He came across Qin's post from years ago.

70
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,520
A photo of him with a friend,

71
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,240
aka

72
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,760
someone he used to flirt with.

73
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,560
That's why he became

74
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,760
a sad boy.

75
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,200
How are you doing?

76
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,880
Just sit.

77
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,720
Nothing much, really.

78
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,520
I met the guy yesterday.

79
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,560
Qin told me that they were friends.

80
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,600
So the teddy bear…

81
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,360
So that's all in the past, right?

82
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,960
If so, then why are you looking all blue?

83
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,200
He said they were friends,

84
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,880
but he still keeps the teddy bear.

85
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,560
- Why didn't he throw it away?
- Yeah.

86
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,280
Why don't you tell him to do so?

87
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,360
Can I really do that?

88
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,840
What?!

89
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,400
Of course you can!

90
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,960
Aren't you guys "talking"?

91
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,880
Do you think I'm brave enough to ask?

92
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:19,280
If I tell him,
but he refuses to throw it away,

93
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,840
I'll be worse than a lost puppy.

94
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,480
Well, you're already are.

95
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:26,520
Plus, it's not looking good for you.

96
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,520
Listen, I don't want you to risk it.

97
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,520
Come on. You're overthinking it.

98
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,160
You won't know until you try, right?

99
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,400
It's okay.

100
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,440
Even if he stops loving you,

101
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,560
we still do, all right?

102
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,480
Jamie…

103
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,920
- Don't go red on us.
- I'll only let Qin kiss me.

104
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,960
My kisses are better than Qin's, you know?

105
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,640
Duang, my baby!

106
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,600
I already ordered you
yuzu ramen with chashu.

107
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,640
No green onions,

108
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,480
extra chashu, and extra noodles.

109
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,880
Anything else you'd like?

110
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,560
You remember I don't like green onions?

111
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:20,360
Of course, why wouldn't I?

112
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,440
You're blushing, aren't you?

113
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:33,000
Nobody else is like you.

114
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,039
You never blush.

115
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,039
I do,

116
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:38,600
but I keep it in my heart.

117
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,480
Gosh.

118
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,080
I don't think that's the case.

119
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,880
Your skin is too thick.

120
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:48,680
Thick but soft, all right?

121
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,200
Do you want to try it?

122
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,200
Place your order already. I'm starving.

123
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,000
Two sets, please.

124
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,520
I saw the Instagram post.

125
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,680
The music students are hosting
a jazz showcase.

126
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,480
It's for a studio class.

127
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,800
Whoa!

128
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,120
Really?

129
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,280
Will you be onstage too?

130
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,160
I have to,

131
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,320
my friends want me to sing.

132
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,240
I don't want to.

133
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,640
Why not?

134
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,560
You're extremely talented.

135
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:40,640
You sing and play guitar very well.

136
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,400
I'm not that great.

137
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,400
You are!

138
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,920
I still remember the day we were onstage.

139
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,400
You were the superstar back there.

140
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,480
You were killing it!

141
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:52,600
Not really.

142
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,720
I almost couldn't finish the song

143
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,240
without you by my side.

144
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,560
You don't want to do it
because I'm not there?

145
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,040
How about this?

146
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:17,440
I'll be there right in front of you.

147
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,160
Just tell me,

148
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,280
and I'll be there.

149
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,080
Do you think

150
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,320
I sound emotionless when I sing?

151
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,560
Don't blame me for this,

152
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,600
but, for me,

153
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,880
just seeing you stand there
already moves me.

154
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,440
But…

155
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,840
I'm not sure
if I can give you an unbiased answer

156
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,960
to what you're looking for.

157
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,640
Forget it.

158
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,920
But your goal is to be a singer, isn't it?

159
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,000
I don't know.

160
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,120
I know that you do.

161
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,480
Honestly,

162
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,480
I want you to trust me
more than anybody else,

163
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,400
but you're stubborn.

164
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,040
You won't listen to what people say.

165
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,120
I think…

166
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:27,120
What's good for you

167
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,840
is to trust yourself.

168
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,720
Here's a trick I'd like to add.

169
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,000
While we were onstage,

170
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,920
I was terrified, you know?

171
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:46,400
But I put all of my fears onto you.

172
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,680
And I want you to do the same.

173
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,040
Although this time,

174
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:00,680
I might not get to go onstage with you,

175
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:03,160
I'll be there in the crowd.

176
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,880
I'll be in the very front row,

177
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,600
the very same spot I fell for you.

178
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:15,440
Put all your worries and fears on me.

179
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,680
I'll take care of them myself.

180
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,240
<i>You free tonight?</i>

181
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,760
<i>Let's party at the same place.</i>

182
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,400
Hey.

183
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,000
Jamie asked if I wanted to drink.

184
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,840
You can go.

185
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:34,880
Wanna go together?

186
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,000
So?

187
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:56,720
Even in this dim light,
you still look like such a badass.

188
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:58,960
Duang, come on now.

189
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,320
I ordered chicken tendons.
I can order more later.

190
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,920
I love you so much, Qin.

191
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:11,120
You can't say
that kind of stuff here, all right?

192
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,360
Know whose man he is?

193
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,520
He's mine!

194
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,480
Well, I want the chicken tendons…

195
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:28,200
Whatever.

196
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:38,160
The girl behind us is fire.

197
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:39,680
Who?

198
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,360
- Hey!
- That table.

199
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,000
What?

200
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,800
What is it?

201
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,760
Qin.

202
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,320
What brings you here?

203
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,520
Hi, guys.

204
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,640
How about a toast?

205
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,640
Cheers.

206
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,080
A toast.

207
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,400
Tonight, aside from him,

208
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:15,960
nobody else asked you to toast, right?

209
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,640
Can I borrow Qin for a bit?

210
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,200
Hey, come with us.

211
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,760
Everyone else want to meet you.

212
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,720
Come on, this way.

213
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,000
I'll be right back.

214
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,960
Right this way.

215
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,600
This way.

216
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:48,800
I'm not borrowing him.

217
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:50,840
I'm taking him back.

218
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:58,960
Think you're cool?

219
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,320
Sit down!

220
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,680
He's a dick, all right?

221
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,240
Take him back? Seriously?

222
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,600
This is upsetting.

223
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,200
I trust Qin,

224
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,720
but not that bastard.

225
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,120
Yeah, I don't trust him either.

226
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,560
He even raised an eyebrow at me.

227
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:24,200
It's hard to believe that
all of us managed to gather here.

228
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,760
Let's play a game. Who's in?

229
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:26,680
- Yeah.
- Sure.

230
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:27,640
Let's play.

231
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:30,440
I watched a series called…
What's it called again?

232
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,600
It's called "Bet" something.

233
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,760
Whatever.

234
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,360
The game's called "Heart Rate."

235
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,360
Clear the table for me.

236
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,280
Let's do this.

237
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:41,200
- What the hell is "Heart Rate"?
- What kind of game is that?

238
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,520
Right.

239
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,520
First.

240
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,000
Jay and Ya, give me your smart watches.

241
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,040
Each of you, give yours to me.

242
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,280
What the hell?

243
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,520
Can't afford a smart watch?

244
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,800
Damn it. These are required for the game.

245
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:56,920
All right.

246
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,720
The rules are simple.

247
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,560
Answer a question,
and if your heart rate goes above 100 bpm,

248
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,000
bottoms up.

249
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,360
- Shit!
- Yo!

250
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,560
- Understood?
- Qin, are you playing?

251
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,760
- Interesting.
- No.

252
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,840
- What? You're not playing?
- Qin!

253
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,600
We never get to hang out.

254
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,520
- Yeah.
- Just play.

255
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,520
Please! Please!

256
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,600
Don't chicken out.

257
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,280
Okay. Let me demonstrate.

258
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:17,800
Kie, play with me.

259
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,400
- Me?
- Yes, you.

260
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,840
- All right. Bring it on!
- Let's see.

261
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,120
Rock, paper, scissors.

262
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,160
The winner goes first.

263
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,960
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

264
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,440
- I win!
- You're first.

265
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,360
All right.

266
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,920
- Cho.
- Yes?

267
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:38,200
When you got spanked in front of everyone
at the morning assembly,

268
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:39,480
you were embarrassed, right?

269
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,480
You laughed so fucking loud, Jay.

270
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,320
It's below 100 bpm, stupid.

271
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,560
My turn.

272
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,960
Dao…

273
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,360
Dao…

274
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,880
You said that you dumped her,

275
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,480
but it was the other way around, no?

276
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,760
What?!

277
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:05,119
- Sheesh!
- What's the truth?

278
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,640
- Explain yourself.
- Gosh.

279
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,680
What's the truth?

280
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,160
It's 110 bpm. You lost!

281
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,440
- Bottoms up!
- Bottoms up!

282
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:16,800
Chug! Chug! Chug!

283
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:22,960
All right. Who's next? You?

284
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,240
I'm out. I'm wasted. Play without me.

285
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:27,319
Jay, you can't play.
You're full of secrets.

286
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,160
Go for it.

287
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,560
I'll play.

288
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:33,400
But under one condition.

289
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,560
I'm playing with Qin.

290
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,480
Damn.

291
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,520
Sheesh.

292
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:41,640
What?

293
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,680
Afraid you'll lose?

294
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,720
Or that you'll lose control?

295
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,480
Damn!

296
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,440
He's taunting him.

297
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:51,560
If you're not up for it,

298
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:52,560
it's okay.

299
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,920
Everyone will know that

300
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:56,920
you're still longing for me.

301
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,400
- Damn!
- Yo!

302
00:17:58,480 --> 00:17:59,560
For real?

303
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,800
He's so damn full of himself.

304
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:06,760
He's giving Qin no fucking choice.

305
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:11,680
- I'm in.
- Here we go!

306
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,560
That's the spirit!

307
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,840
- This is a fun night.
- What a match this is.

308
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:17,680
All right. Make it nice and tight.

309
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:32,800
You refused my love
because you have commitment issues, no?

310
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,440
Shit…

311
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,320
- Shit…
- This first question is a tough one.

312
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:41,720
I guess not.

313
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,840
You intentionally ghosted me, didn't you?

314
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,720
I'm preparing a shot just for you.

315
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,600
It's going up! Damn!

316
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,720
The teddy I gave you…

317
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,440
You still have it, don't you?

318
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:06,640
- What a question?!
- Damn!

319
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,600
- Sheesh!
- Response?

320
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:11,120
An old flame is being rekindled!

321
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,440
It's waiting to be reignited!

322
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,400
<i>The one who came after</i>

323
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,120
- What?
- Hey, that's not it.

324
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,760
You came back for me now
because you regret losing me, right?

325
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,160
- Damn!
- Regret, hey?

326
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,240
Close…

327
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,320
- It's close.
- Do you want a shot now?

328
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,040
It's so close!

329
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,720
- It's close, Tiw!
- Damn, it's 99!

330
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,400
Hey Tiw. You're going to lose!

331
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,480
You asked me that

332
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,520
because you still like me, right?

333
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,160
Shit!

334
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,600
Straight to the point.

335
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,040
- It's rising.
- It's serious.

336
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,360
Here we go!

337
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,520
Here we go! This is it!

338
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:28,160
The tables have turned!

339
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:36,280
Chug! Chug! Chug!

340
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,960
Chug…

341
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,720
Chug…

342
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:42,320
Hey.

343
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,600
Be honest.

344
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:46,120
Do you two still feel the same way?

345
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,120
I'm kidding.

346
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,000
Where are you going?

347
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:58,520
Let's talk outside.

348
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:00,800
There's nothing to say.

349
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,920
We can talk at your table.

350
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:08,920
Why cause trouble?

351
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,040
What?

352
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:11,680
Can't I sit at your table?

353
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,200
Where is he taking Qin to?

354
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:24,880
Duang, this is the moment.

355
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,440
Go after them.

356
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,480
Hey.

357
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,800
Now's not the time.

358
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:29,920
Let them talk.

359
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,400
Duang can clear things up later.

360
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:35,440
I don't think Qin is an irrational person.
Think about it.

361
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,240
Pae…

362
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:39,080
He can't give up.

363
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:41,280
If they reconcile,

364
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,000
then who is Duang in this relationship?

365
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,120
I agree with him though.

366
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:46,920
I told you.

367
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:49,680
There are two conditions for me
to stop chasing Qin.

368
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,400
If he wants to get back with that guy,

369
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,840
then I'm out, right?

370
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:59,160
Damn it.
You're called a lover boy for a reason.

371
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,480
Is this really what you want?

372
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:04,400
Duang, get a grip.

373
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:05,440
Who are you?

374
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,960
What are you saying?

375
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,120
Who the hell are you?
I don't know who this is.

376
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,280
The Duang that I know

377
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,800
always fights till the end.

378
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,920
Hey.

379
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,160
Listen to me.

380
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:20,000
If you don't want to be a sad puppy
like Pae said,

381
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:22,480
then go after Qin.

382
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,200
Wait!

383
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,840
If he's going to punch you,
make sure to scream, okay?

384
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,120
- We'll be there.
- Okay!

385
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,040
Is he going to be okay?

386
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:36,520
We're not going to go after him?

387
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:39,280
I think Qin can handle this.

388
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:41,600
Let Duang hear it from Qin's mouth.

389
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,480
My heart was racing
because of someone else, not you.

390
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,360
So now you can explain how you feel?

391
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,040
You said nothing before.

392
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:49,960
That's why no one can be with you.

393
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,160
Tiw.

394
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,320
You've gone too far.

395
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,880
I know you better than anyone else.

396
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,720
That's why I'm saying this.

397
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,640
Then you probably knew

398
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,440
I was starting to fall for you back then.

399
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,400
I loved you once, Tiw.

400
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,000
I just want to know…

401
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,880
what did I do wrong
trying to take it slow?

402
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:47,040
Hey, wait.

403
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:49,440
Where's Tiw?

404
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,000
I don't know.

405
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,400
You two are in the talking stage,
aren't you?

406
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:57,320
Why don't you ask him yourself?

407
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,320
I'm off to practice now.

408
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,000
<i>I never fucking understood it.</i>

409
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,000
<i>When you wanted me, you gave it your all.</i>

410
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,680
But when I tried to love you back…

411
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:18,760
Why did you give up on me?

412
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:20,080
Why did you disappear?

413
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:22,480
- Why did you--
- Not everyone can wait for you.

414
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,720
It's true I started at 100,

415
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,920
but no one can stay like that forever.

416
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,840
People lose hope too, you know.

417
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,360
It felt like trying to fill
a bottomless hole with love.

418
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,400
And?

419
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,000
How long did you expect me to wait?

420
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,880
Have you ever tried
seeing it from my perspective?

421
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:41,200
If you didn't love me anymore,
just tell me.

422
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:42,400
Why find someone else?

423
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,920
Where's Tiw?

424
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,920
No clue.

425
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,440
What?

426
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,760
You two are usually glued to each other.

427
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:04,400
Yeah.

428
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:05,840
I'm heading home now.

429
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:13,800
Hey, Tiw. Where are you going?

430
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:15,760
I'm busy.

431
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,600
I've got a date with Sea.

432
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,520
Who's that?

433
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,560
You'll find out soon.

434
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:23,640
See you.

435
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,280
Tiw.

436
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:32,880
I heard you're dating someone new?

437
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:34,960
How could you do that to Qin?

438
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:37,200
What did I do?

439
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,840
There's nothing between us.

440
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:41,520
What do you mean?

441
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,920
You two are in…

442
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,720
the talking stage, aren't you?

443
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:48,400
Is that what you call it?

444
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:51,120
It's very one-sided.

445
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,680
That's not true.

446
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:54,960
How is that not true?

447
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,880
I asked him about us,

448
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:58,720
but he wouldn't say a word.

449
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,040
What do you expect me to do?

450
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:03,080
You have no idea how torturous it's been.

451
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,480
It's a one-sided relationship.

452
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,080
Like throwing my love away.

453
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:09,040
Never knowing how he feels.

454
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:11,480
I'm not staying.

455
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,280
Then why don't you tell Qin?

456
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:18,120
You want me to do that?

457
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,240
For what?

458
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,720
Qin won't change himself for anyone.

459
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,400
<i>That hurt like hell, you know?</i>

460
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:30,040
I wish I could cry like everyone else,

461
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,120
but I couldn't.

462
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:34,160
Being heartbroken
and unable to cry hurt so much.

463
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,560
But that's okay.

464
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,800
I was good on my own.

465
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,840
I just had to get back to my life

466
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:43,760
without you.

467
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,120
It's too late to now, Qin.

468
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:49,600
I didn't realize it
until I was dating someone else.

469
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,120
- What did you realize?
- I regretted it.

470
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,680
I want to ask you one question.

471
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,680
Just one question.

472
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:02,560
Just tell me

473
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,920
you still feel the same.

474
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,320
And that'll be it.

475
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:09,840
- Tiw…
- How about we start dating?

476
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:10,160
Wait, Qin.

477
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:12,440
- Let go of me.
- We're not done.

478
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:14,120
Where are you going?

479
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:19,480
We weren't done last time
because you fucking ran away.

480
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:20,960
What do you want from me now?

481
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,520
I'm not running away this time.

482
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,320
Duang! Duang!

483
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,600
Duang…

484
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:32,080
Watch the table for me.

485
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,280
Right…

486
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,960
What the hell?

487
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:40,520
Let's settle this here,

488
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,040
so you can get out of my life.

489
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:43,960
Sure.

490
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:44,880
Let's do this.

491
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:47,120
I'm not someone you can just break up with

492
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:49,080
and come back to whenever you want.

493
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,360
Whether you come back or not,

494
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:54,080
it's all the same to me.

495
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,520
- Nothing has changed.
- It's because of Duang, right?

496
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,800
How'd it go?

497
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:05,640
Where's Duang?

498
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,240
He went out the back door.

499
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:08,680
He walked out looking all upset.

500
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:11,640
He took off in a taxi.

501
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,440
He's not picking up.

502
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:19,880
No reply here either.

503
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,880
Where do you think he went?

504
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,840
Shit.

505
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:29,680
He's usually only with you.

506
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:31,440
He's right.

507
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:32,680
But there's still hope.

508
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,680
He couldn't have gone far.

509
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:36,520
How about you check your place first?

510
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,160
Maybe he's there.

511
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:40,080
Want me to come with you?

512
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:42,800
It's okay. I'll go alone.

513
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:44,720
I'll clear everything up.

514
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:46,800
Okay.

515
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:41,880
QIN IS CALLING YOU

516
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:53,840
<i>It's because of Duang, right?</i>

517
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:56,520
Why him?

518
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:58,720
Why does it matter to you?

519
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:00,600
Because it's not fair to me!

520
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:02,640
I came into your life the same way he did!

521
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:05,000
All my posts were about you!

522
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,680
<i>I can't explain why it's him</i>

523
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:11,800
when everyone else did the same thing.

524
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:14,560
But as time went on,

525
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,920
I realized he was more special
than the others.

526
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,640
So he changed you this much, huh?

527
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:23,720
You're not the Qin I knew.

528
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:39,800
<i>I'm back at my place.</i>

529
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,120
<i>If you're not coming back…</i>

530
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,960
<i>then don't come back at all.</i>

531
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,880
I haven't changed, Tiw.

532
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:59,480
It's just that I've never shown
this side of me to anyone before.

533
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:08,200
<i>I'll give you 15 more minutes.</i>

534
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:18,280
I hope you regret
choosing someone like him.

535
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,800
I trust him.

536
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,120
He won't let me down, Tiw.

537
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:41,920
Why didn't you pick up?

538
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:50,120
I was scared you'd tell me
to get out of your life.

539
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:54,680
And…

540
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:56,840
Did I make it in time?

541
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:00,600
You did.

542
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,120
If I were late, would you--

543
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,720
I'd wait until you did.

544
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:19,040
You heard us, right?

545
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:23,840
I did.

546
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,280
How much did you hear?

547
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,720
So you just assumed the rest?

548
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:44,160
Why didn't you come to me, Duang?

549
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,440
I needed you the most.

550
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:52,080
He asked you to be his boyfriend.

551
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:54,840
If I'd said yes,
why would I ask you to come here?

552
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:56,040
To clear things up.

553
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:58,440
There's nothing to clear up.

554
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,520
What about how he made your heart race?

555
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:07,000
Because you looked like
you were about to cry.

556
00:34:17,239 --> 00:34:19,080
I never gave up on you, you know?

557
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:23,320
But when I'm with you,

558
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,679
it feels like
someone else already has your heart.

559
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:32,239
Even if I chose you,

560
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,639
would you still feel that way?

561
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:39,280
I'm worried we'll get stuck just talking

562
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,960
and end up as friends.

563
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:43,920
I never thought of you as a friend.

564
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:49,360
I didn't tell you everything
about Tiw and me

565
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:51,560
because I wanted to see what you'd do.

566
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:53,760
I admit it.

567
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,840
I used Tiw as the benchmark for you.

568
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:58,520
But I also admit that

569
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:01,280
you went way beyond that, Duang.

570
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:05,960
Even though I'm not good with words,

571
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:09,080
I'll prove it to you,

572
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:12,600
just like you did for me.

573
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:51,920
I choose you.

574
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:54,840
Any questions?

575
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:03,200
You're not the only one
who feels this way.

576
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:05,960
Now I feel the same way about you

577
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:12,440
as you do about me.

578
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,480
Anything you want me to change?

579
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:30,920
I mean…

580
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,720
If it helps improve things between us.

581
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:40,120
Are things between us bad currently?

582
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:41,760
No, not like that.

583
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:45,160
I started to wonder

584
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,080
how bad things would be

585
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:49,920
if one day you weren't around.

586
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:52,720
What should I do

587
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,640
to keep you by my side?

588
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,360
I can't promise you
that things will always be good.

589
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:08,240
But I will always be by your side.

590
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:17,160
I couldn't go on without you either.

591
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:23,240
And I'm delighted
that I get to be with you every day.

592
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,040
You're amazing

593
00:38:30,240 --> 00:38:31,880
for making me feel like this, you know?

594
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,000
Better now?

595
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,680
Yes.

596
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,160
I've been okay

597
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,000
since the day you said,

598
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:53,280
"Good luck with that then."

599
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,480
You still remember it?

600
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:58,240
Of course I do, if it's about you.

601
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,920
Gosh…

602
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,920
I was a chicken back then.

603
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,440
You called yourself a chicken?

604
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:08,200
I practiced it with Jamie so much,
I creeped him out.

605
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:11,280
Why do you like me so much?

606
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,280
Right?

607
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:19,680
I don't know why I like you this much.

608
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:23,720
Actually…

609
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:27,600
I might understand you

610
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:33,320
because I've been asking myself every day

611
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,120
why I love you this much.

612
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,000
Auntie Joo!

613
00:40:25,080 --> 00:40:26,600
- What?!
- You're closed already?

614
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:28,080
Gosh…

615
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:30,120
Take a look around.

616
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:31,440
Of course we're closed.

617
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:32,720
So…

618
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:36,600
My man and I are very hungry,
and we really want garlic shrimp.

619
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:37,520
Gosh…

620
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,280
The cooks have already gone home.

621
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:41,000
Nobody's here. I'm just closing up.

622
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:42,440
What should we do then?

623
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,360
Wait…

624
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,160
Do you have the ingredients?

625
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:46,640
We know how to cook the dish.

626
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:48,080
I mean, I can cook it.

627
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,880
- You can?
- I can.

628
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:53,240
Shrimp's in the freezer.
Clean the pan once you're done.

629
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:54,480
You're really gonna let us?

630
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,280
You've come this far.

631
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,440
Come on. Go.

632
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:58,920
Go get it done. Hurry.

633
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,160
Okay. Thank you!

634
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:02,200
- Gosh, where was I?
- Thank you.

635
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:04,240
Why not make it at home?

636
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,800
These guys…

637
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:07,440
Where was I?

638
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,560
You can cook, right?

639
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:11,520
I've got this. Don't worry.

640
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:14,920
This is nothing! It's not hard at all.

641
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,400
This is me you're talking about.

642
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:19,920
What?

643
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:29,600
Wait.

644
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:33,440
We need to add a dash of love.

645
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:51,920
Watch out.

646
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:23,840
Why are you smiling?

647
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:27,480
Do you know that

648
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:30,320
everything you do looks so sweet?

649
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,880
Dig in already.
You've got class in the morning.

650
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:39,160
You've also got class at 10:00 a.m.

651
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:44,120
Yours is at 8:30 a.m.

652
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:51,840
You know my schedule?

653
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,800
You remember mine,

654
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,400
and I remember yours.

655
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:05,680
I want to give you
as much as you've given me.

656
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:29,600
Dig in, please.

657
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:33,200
What a combo!

658
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:35,680
"Dig in, please."

659
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:44,960
Let's dig in.

660
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:48,120
It's all yours,

661
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:51,640
the shrimp and my heart.

662
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:20,920
I'm taking a shower.

663
00:46:39,920 --> 00:46:41,920
Hello, Jettana. Hello, Prachai.

664
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:43,440
Sheesh!

665
00:46:43,520 --> 00:46:46,400
Duang is looking cool today.

666
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:48,120
Did you clear things up?

667
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,800
Don't tell me your wearing those
to hide a bruise.

668
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:52,600
I just want to look cool.

669
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:54,480
Your eyes must be swollen.

670
00:46:54,560 --> 00:46:56,560
Care for a visit to Gangnam Clinic?

671
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:58,280
Where? What?

672
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:00,320
Go and get your face treated.

673
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:01,320
GANGNAM CLINIC
CHAT

674
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:03,560
There's a promotion too, you know?

675
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:08,520
Add their LINE ID: @gangnamclinic
and get a free laser hair removal session.

676
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:09,880
What?! Show me!

677
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:11,200
That's so interesting.

678
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:13,600
Let me add their LINE.
I want a free session.

679
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:15,320
- Hey, wait…
- Hey!

680
00:47:17,240 --> 00:47:18,120
Look at you.

681
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:20,080
- I knew it.
- Hey, Pae!

682
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:21,680
You got dumped by Qin?

683
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:23,040
I'll slap you in the face.

684
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:24,320
I'm not heartbroken.

685
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:26,880
It's love pouring out from my eyes!

686
00:47:28,320 --> 00:47:29,280
Well, that's great.

687
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:30,400
Are you guys dating now?

688
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:32,360
Not yet,

689
00:47:32,440 --> 00:47:34,480
but I think I'm almost there.

690
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,000
You're still not his boyfriend?

691
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:37,520
What keeps you waiting?

692
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:40,600
I still feel like I'm not good enough.

693
00:47:41,880 --> 00:47:43,200
Just a puppy.

694
00:47:43,280 --> 00:47:44,920
Only God is better than you.

695
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:47,920
I'm too afraid to ask Qin.

696
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:50,040
Man up, then.

697
00:47:50,120 --> 00:47:51,960
And fulfill the vows
you made at the temples.

698
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:53,880
You made vows at a lot of temples.

699
00:47:53,960 --> 00:47:55,920
You're still young.

700
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:57,360
If it's a no, just cut ties.

701
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:01,120
My scissors aren't sharp,

702
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:02,520
so they can't cut any ties!

703
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:03,520
All right?

704
00:48:03,600 --> 00:48:05,760
- Sheesh!
- So corny.

705
00:48:07,800 --> 00:48:09,400
Gosh, I'm done with you guys.

706
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:10,920
I'm getting a cup of dark roast.

707
00:48:12,240 --> 00:48:15,160
Your tears weren't bitter enough?

708
00:48:15,240 --> 00:48:16,800
I'm going to smack you!

709
00:48:16,880 --> 00:48:19,240
- Gosh!
- He's too flustered to take it.

710
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:25,080
Wait up!

711
00:48:27,560 --> 00:48:29,160
Qin is here!

712
00:48:32,320 --> 00:48:33,640
What's going on?

713
00:48:33,720 --> 00:48:35,840
It's about that thing.

714
00:48:35,920 --> 00:48:37,800
- It's about that.
- That?

715
00:48:37,880 --> 00:48:40,680
Three, two, one…

716
00:48:40,760 --> 00:48:42,560
Please join our band!

717
00:48:45,920 --> 00:48:48,040
We really need you to carry us.

718
00:48:48,120 --> 00:48:49,800
We need to submit names.

719
00:48:49,880 --> 00:48:52,400
Please join us. Please, please!

720
00:48:52,480 --> 00:48:54,720
- You can think about it later.
- Okay.

721
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:57,880
What did you just say?

722
00:48:57,960 --> 00:48:59,920
I said okay. I'm in.

723
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:07,440
- When do we practice?
- Tomorrow!

724
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:10,320
Wait, why did you
suddenly change your mind?

725
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:12,440
Well…

726
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:14,200
He…

727
00:49:14,680 --> 00:49:15,520
Duang convinced me.

728
00:49:17,960 --> 00:49:19,360
So what's the deal between you?

729
00:49:19,440 --> 00:49:20,880
Give us an update, will you?

730
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:22,680
We're dying to know.

731
00:49:22,760 --> 00:49:24,480
Are you guys a couple?

732
00:49:24,560 --> 00:49:26,800
Or more than a couple?

733
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:29,120
What's it going to be?

734
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,280
We're still just talking.

735
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:34,000
- How upsetting!
- How upsetting!

736
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:34,920
Right.

737
00:49:35,000 --> 00:49:36,160
Change your status already.

738
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:38,240
- Yeah.
- You're this close to him.

739
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:40,520
Yeah, just date him already.

740
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,280
We've been waiting for ages!

741
00:49:47,520 --> 00:49:48,960
You upset him.

742
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:51,840
Long live Duang!

743
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:53,400
Long live Duang!

744
00:49:53,480 --> 00:49:54,880
Long live Duang!

745
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:56,680
Long live Duang!

746
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:57,640
Did we embarrass him?

747
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:07,120
A hot nerd…

748
00:50:10,120 --> 00:50:11,720
Surprise!

749
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:22,480
My darling Marvis-chan.

750
00:50:22,560 --> 00:50:23,720
Yes.

751
00:50:23,800 --> 00:50:25,240
What would you like?

752
00:50:27,200 --> 00:50:28,200
No?

753
00:50:29,720 --> 00:50:32,640
I'm sorry.

754
00:50:32,720 --> 00:50:34,200
Did I ruin the mood?

755
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:36,960
No, I'm just stressed out about work.

756
00:50:42,440 --> 00:50:44,200
Want me to help you?

757
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:48,080
Not that I'm boasting,
but I'm a Decorative Arts student.

758
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:52,840
Draw me something then.

759
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:53,880
Sure.

760
00:50:53,960 --> 00:50:55,200
I'll show you.

761
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:56,880
I've always had what it takes.

762
00:51:00,280 --> 00:51:01,800
How did you get here, by the way?

763
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:05,080
I wanted a cup of coffee, so I came here.

764
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:08,880
Then I spotted you, cutie.
So I came over to say hi.

765
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:13,640
Do you use cheesy lines like that a lot?

766
00:51:14,720 --> 00:51:16,680
I don't. But…

767
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:21,200
Drinking from this cup
is basically an indirect kiss.

768
00:51:21,280 --> 00:51:23,240
I'll get you a new one.

769
00:51:24,320 --> 00:51:26,160
Why an indirect kiss?

770
00:51:26,240 --> 00:51:27,560
Can't it simply be a kiss?

771
00:51:41,400 --> 00:51:43,080
It's cocoa, right? I'll go get it.

772
00:51:51,640 --> 00:51:52,680
Here.

773
00:52:01,280 --> 00:52:02,200
Here.

774
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:04,360
Sketch something for me.

775
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:21,520
Clinging to me this tightly…

776
00:52:21,600 --> 00:52:23,160
How am I supposed to draw like this?

777
00:52:24,720 --> 00:52:26,600
Well, it's cold.

778
00:52:26,680 --> 00:52:28,080
I forgot to bring my jacket.

779
00:52:28,160 --> 00:52:29,720
Can I borrow your arm?

780
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:32,600
Okay, okay.

781
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:34,600
What do you want me to draw?

782
00:52:36,040 --> 00:52:38,120
Me. Just simple.

783
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:41,160
Right.

784
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:42,760
All right.

785
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,240
There!

786
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:05,040
Hey!

787
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:06,800
What?

788
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:08,600
It looks just like you.

789
00:53:09,280 --> 00:53:10,680
Try again.

790
00:53:10,760 --> 00:53:12,640
I don't want to look like a dog.

791
00:53:12,720 --> 00:53:15,000
I don't want to look at you

792
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:16,600
because whenever I do,

793
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:19,200
you always give me those pleading eyes.

794
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:20,640
It's turning me on.

795
00:53:22,040 --> 00:53:23,400
Please.

796
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:26,040
All right. I'm serious this time.

797
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:55,160
Look.

798
00:53:58,720 --> 00:53:59,680
That's really cool.

799
00:54:00,600 --> 00:54:02,440
You're buttering me up.

800
00:54:03,200 --> 00:54:04,440
Buttering you up?

801
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:09,720
You really are that great.

802
00:54:10,320 --> 00:54:12,200
So you don't have any more classes?

803
00:54:12,280 --> 00:54:14,200
Nope, class is done for the day.

804
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:16,800
Well…

805
00:54:17,360 --> 00:54:18,640
Do you want to go shopping?

806
00:54:18,720 --> 00:54:20,240
I don't want to work anymore.

807
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:24,320
So I'm the bad influence here?

808
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:27,440
It's fine. My assignment isn't urgent.

809
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:29,240
I'm the one rushing it.

810
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:31,640
Then let's go.

811
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:34,280
I'll take care of your iPad.

812
00:54:57,240 --> 00:54:58,840
I was just asking.

813
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,840
I didn't think you'd take me here today.

814
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:04,800
The jazz showcase is soon.
I'm running out of time.

815
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:08,240
So you'll be joining in?

816
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:10,880
That's great.

817
00:55:10,960 --> 00:55:13,400
I'll take film photos of you there.

818
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:27,800
You know what?

819
00:55:27,880 --> 00:55:30,440
That day we ran into each other…

820
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:33,920
I swear I didn't follow you here. Wait!

821
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:36,200
I did find this place on your Insta.

822
00:55:36,280 --> 00:55:37,360
Wait!

823
00:55:37,440 --> 00:55:38,520
But I didn't follow you.

824
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:40,400
Wait, I still followed you here.

825
00:55:40,480 --> 00:55:41,640
I mean…

826
00:55:41,720 --> 00:55:43,280
I know you didn't mean to.

827
00:55:43,360 --> 00:55:45,160
If you did, you wouldn't look so shocked.

828
00:55:49,040 --> 00:55:50,040
What's for dinner?

829
00:55:55,120 --> 00:55:56,120
Up to you.

830
00:56:00,480 --> 00:56:02,640
How about Greyhound? Your favorite.

831
00:56:07,160 --> 00:56:09,600
What would you do
if I kissed you right now?

832
00:56:10,680 --> 00:56:11,880
Such a dirty mind.

833
00:56:11,960 --> 00:56:13,160
Stop being so cute then.

834
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:14,880
How am I being cute?

835
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:18,000
Remembering my favorite restaurant
already melts my heart.

836
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:21,200
So the way you remember
what I like and dislike…

837
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:22,360
what do you call that?

838
00:56:23,280 --> 00:56:25,720
Go on, give me a compliment. I'm waiting.

839
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:28,960
So very cute…

840
00:56:32,280 --> 00:56:33,760
At this rate, I might die!

841
00:56:33,840 --> 00:56:35,480
I don't need anything else.

842
00:56:36,080 --> 00:56:39,160
Fine, I'll just drive us
straight into the barrier then.

843
00:56:41,200 --> 00:56:42,800
You're so funny.

844
00:56:42,880 --> 00:56:43,800
You're such a pain.

845
00:56:47,640 --> 00:56:48,760
Excuse me.

846
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:52,680
Do you have the Contax T3?

847
00:56:53,440 --> 00:56:56,040
No, we don't.

848
00:56:56,120 --> 00:56:57,800
But if you come across one, let me know.

849
00:56:59,120 --> 00:57:00,520
Okay, thank you.

850
00:57:01,040 --> 00:57:01,880
Come on, let's go.

851
00:57:02,840 --> 00:57:03,760
Okay!

852
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,000
Let's go!

853
00:58:56,960 --> 00:58:58,560
Hey, not now!

854
00:59:11,720 --> 00:59:12,880
Eyes on the road.

855
00:59:12,960 --> 00:59:14,280
Here.

856
00:59:31,840 --> 00:59:33,480
<i>Do you have the Contax T3?</i>

857
00:59:34,920 --> 00:59:36,240
<i>We don't have any here.</i>

858
00:59:42,440 --> 00:59:45,000
<i>If you get one, please let me know.</i>

859
01:00:14,960 --> 01:00:15,800
Duang.

860
01:00:22,680 --> 01:00:23,520
Do you know why

861
01:00:25,240 --> 01:00:28,400
I decided to sing in the jazz showcase?

862
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:34,840
Because you believe you can do it?

863
01:00:36,800 --> 01:00:37,880
You know me too well.

864
01:00:38,440 --> 01:00:40,360
Not going to give yourself some credit?

865
01:00:42,160 --> 01:00:43,080
No.

866
01:00:43,720 --> 01:00:45,360
The credit is all yours.

867
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:47,680
Is there anything you want to tell me

868
01:00:48,440 --> 01:00:49,920
about how you're feeling?

869
01:00:56,800 --> 01:00:58,960
I know I can do things well,

870
01:01:01,600 --> 01:01:02,760
but before now,

871
01:01:05,200 --> 01:01:07,000
I never believed in my own abilities.

872
01:01:09,720 --> 01:01:10,960
Thank you…

873
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:14,080
for helping me believe in myself.

874
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:20,080
And thank you…

875
01:01:22,120 --> 01:01:23,320
for believing in me.

876
01:04:14,320 --> 01:04:15,880
This is for the College of Music?

877
01:04:15,960 --> 01:04:16,840
Correct!

878
01:04:16,920 --> 01:04:18,880
Give it up for our new leader!

879
01:04:18,960 --> 01:04:20,360
<i>I'll probably miss you so much</i>

880
01:04:20,440 --> 01:04:22,040
that I'll die for sure.

881
01:04:23,040 --> 01:04:27,000
<i>Is it bad that everyone says</i>
<i>you're my boyfriend?</i>

882
01:04:27,080 --> 01:04:28,600
But we're not boyfriends.

883
01:04:28,680 --> 01:04:30,160
How much coffee did you drink?

884
01:04:30,240 --> 01:04:31,880
<i>Do you think it makes me happy</i>

885
01:04:31,960 --> 01:04:33,520
to see you sick?

886
01:04:34,720 --> 01:04:36,720
<i>If I don't ask you now,</i>

887
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:38,480
I'll probably go insane.
